Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Relation/domain
Synopsis Domain of a binary relation: a set consisting of the first element of each tuple.
Function set[&T0] domain (rel[&T0,&T1] R)
Examples 
rascal>import Relation;
ok
rascal>domain({<1,10>, <2,20>});
set[int]: {2,1}
rascal>domain({<"mon", 1>, <"tue", 2>});
set[str]: {"mon","tue"}
